article_text:
It's a place unlike any other in the world and it happens to be in Wisconsin.

Thanks to extremely cold temperatures this season, you can get a rare up-close look at Mother Nature's beauty on the South Shore at the Apostle Islands National Lakeshore in Wisconsin.

The journey to see them is not an easy one. However, after hiking the mile-long trek over snow and Lake Superior ice; many say it's all worth it.
